incidentReports.details: Missing feed data due to ec2 instance failure and failover procedure.
Missing data due to AWS PrivateLink VPC colocation disabled by OKX for Tardis.
Missing data due to AWS PrivateLink VPC colocation networking issue.
Missing data (~40 seconds) caused by moving OKX data collection infrastructure from Tokyo GKE cluster to AWS HongKong (AWS PrivateLink VPC colocation).
Missing data due to a bug that incorrectly assumed that data recording process was unhealthy and killed it causing data loss. Proper fix for this issue was deployed.
GKE node network issue resulted triggering auto-repair logic and missing data in that period.
Missing data due to virtual machine crash. Crash was caused by hardware issue on the physical machine hosting VM which has been automatically replaced with healthy one by auto-repair logic.
Data gaps due to Cloudflare network issue that caused disconnects, high latency, and other connectivity failures, details: https://www.cloudflarestatus.com/incidents/q5wzxr0jhn90
Missing initial order book snapshots for swaps instruments. Issue has been identified and new version with fix deployed.
Intermittent Kubernetes Node network issue caused increased disconnections count and establishing connection timeouts that resulted in missing data.
Missing data (~7 seconds) caused by moving OKEx Swap data collection infrastructure from London to Tokyo GKE cluster.

Increased disconnections count that was caused by OKEx API returning real-time data with too large delay (over 10 seconds). This issue has been reported also by other API users and could cause some data missing (due to disconnects). Since then we have switched to wss://awspush.okex.com:8443/ws/v3 WebSocket endpoint which seems to be more stable in that regard in comparison to default wss://real.okex.com:8443/ws/v3.

K8S node where recording containers are running became unresponsive (network issue, no access to or from node) and has been automatically replaced with healthy node by auto-repair logic. Unfortunately that caused missing data feed for approximately 15 minutes.
